Feature: the agent-vault broker substitutes the stored GitHub credential on a BC's outbound request, with no credential leaving the container

  SB-2 broker arm (PDR-017 §3 SB-2; ADR-028 D2/D3 — the honest home for the relocated,
  formerly-tautological launcher scenario @scenario_hash:f23dfbe84c899968). This is the
  lead-owned integration check that finally EXERCISES the OPEN ADR-026 D2 GitHub-
  brokering mechanism question against the real compose-stood broker, rather than
  asserting it from the launcher's blind side. A BC performs an authenticated GitHub
  operation (e.g. a push to a private beads remote) with no host gh/gitconfig mount and
  no BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME; the broker injects the stored GitHub credential onto the
  forwarded request. Lead-owned integration check against the real broker.
  @scenario_hash:1b077fab23d3baaa
  Scenario: a BC's authenticated GitHub push succeeds through the broker with no host credential mount and no BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME
    Given the agent-vault broker is running on the shopsystem network provisioned with the real GitHub credential
    And a BC container is running with no host gh or gitconfig credential mount and the launch required no BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME
    When the BC performs an authenticated GitHub push to origin through the broker
    Then the push completes successfully against GitHub
    And the request the broker forwards to github.com carries the broker-stored GitHub credential
    And the request as it leaves the container carries no GitHub credential
